place.name: ASWARDBY
place.gazetteerText: ASWARDBY, a parish in Spilsby district, Lincoln; on the river Steeping, 4 miles NW of Spilsby, and 6 SW of Alford r. station. Post Town, Hagworthingham under Spilsby. Acres, 741. Real property, £1,755. Pop., 68. Houses, 15. The property is all in one estate. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £266. Patron, R. Brackenbury, Esq. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
